    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">von Holleben</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23,
                                1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: Acting under
                            instructions from my Government, and in order to settle the legal tender
                            question in Samoa, I have the honor to suggest to you that our
                            Tepresentatives in Apia shall be directed to inform the Samoan
                            Government that the exclusion of German coin is against the Samoan
                            treaty, and that German coin must be admitted into Samoa just as well as
                            United States and British coin, 20 marks to be taken as worth $4.76.</p>
                <p>I have the honor, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holleben.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
